oc:kn_00e800a0 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating proposal templates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never write proposals over 10 pages, use generic uncustomized templates, or bury pricing. Aim for 5-7 pages, customize the executive summary at minimum, and present pricing transparently." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Long generic proposals signal low effort and don't get read" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_49ff68e2 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating structured sales content output" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## {Asset_Type} for {Company}

### Slide/Section 1: {Title}
**Headline:** {one-sentence value statement}
**Body:** {2-3 bullet points}
**Speaker notes/Talk track:** {what to say}
**Visual direction:** {layout guidance}""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Asset_Type",
        "Company",
        "Title" .

oc:kn_4a68c8c0 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing copy for any sales asset" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every claim must connect to revenue, efficiency, or risk reduction. Replace 'AI-powered analytics' with 'cut reporting time by 80%.' Features mean nothing without the 'so what.'" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Buyers buy outcomes, not features — abstract claims are ignored" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4a8ebf21 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating demo scripts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never demo before discovery. If you don't know the prospect's pain, you're guessing which features matter. Always customize demos to their use case, terminology, and workflow." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Premature demos waste time and fail to connect features to buyer needs" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_6f9e6610 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building sales decks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never create a deck that is a feature dump, has 200+ words per slide, lacks a story arc from problem to solution to proof, uses generic screenshots without callouts, or exceeds 12 slides for a standard pitch." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These anti-patterns cause prospects to tune out and reps to abandon the deck" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_817fc235 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any sales enablement work" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Gather before starting: 1) Value proposition and differentiators, 2) Sales motion (self-serve, inside, field, hybrid), deal size, cycle length, 3) Specific collateral needs, funnel stage, user persona, 4) Current state of materials and what reps ask for most." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing context leads to generic output that doesn't match the actual selling situation" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_87318274 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When delivering final output for any sales asset" ;
    oc:directiveContent """| Asset | Deliverable |
|-------|------------|
| Sales deck | Slide-by-slide outline with headline, body copy, and speaker notes |
| One-pager | Full copy with layout guidance (visual hierarchy, sections) |
| Objection doc | Table format: objection, response, proof point, follow-up |
| Demo script | Scene-by-scene with timing, talk track, and interaction points |
| ROI calculator | Input fields, formulas, output display with sample data |
| Playbook | Structured document with table of contents and sections |
| Persona card | One-page card format per persona |
| Proposal | Section-by-section copy with customization notes |""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Asset",
        "Deliverable" .

oc:kn_a2bbbbb5 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning or creating any sales asset" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Tailor every asset to persona, deal stage, and use case. A deck for a CTO should look different from one for a VP of Sales. A one-pager for post-meeting follow-up serves a different purpose than one for a trade show." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Generic materials fail because different buyers evaluate on different criteria" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a67964ac a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before generating any sales collateral" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before starting any asset creation, check for .agents/product-marketing-context.md (or .claude/product-marketing-context.md). If it exists, read it and use that context, only asking for information not already covered." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Avoids redundant questions and ensures consistency with established positioning" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b2343706 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining skill scope" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Sales enablement covers internal materials (battle cards, objection handling, talk tracks). For public-facing competitor comparison pages, defer to competitor-alternatives. For marketing website copy, defer to copywriting. For cold outreach emails, defer to cold-email." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Clear boundaries prevent overlap and ensure the right expertise is applied" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b7680efb a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When formatting and designing any sales document" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Reps need information in 3 seconds, not 30. Use bold headers, short bullets, and visual hierarchy. If a rep can't find the answer mid-call, the doc has failed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sales reps reference materials during live conversations — scannability is survival" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_bf25fc07 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any sales collateral" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Sales uses what sales trusts. Involve reps in creation, use their language not marketing's. If reps rewrite your deck before sending it, you wrote the wrong deck. Test drafts with top performers first." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Materials that don't match how reps actually sell get abandoned and wasted" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ceb2ec22 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring any sales deck or pitch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Sales decks follow a story arc: Situation (problem) → Complication (cost of inaction) → Resolution (your approach, proof, path forward). Never start with your company or product — start with the buyer's world." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Narrative arcs create emotional engagement and make the solution feel inevitable rather than sold" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d2336751 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating or maintaining sales playbooks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Keep playbooks living documents — review quarterly, get input from top reps, remove anything outdated. Assign an owner. If nobody owns it, it rots." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Stale playbooks get ignored and actively harm sales effectiveness" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_fc73ae97 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any sales enablement asset" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Check for product-marketing-context.md and read if exists. 2. Gather missing context: value prop, sales motion, collateral needs, current state. 3. Determine asset type and target persona/stage. 4. Build asset using the appropriate framework (deck=10-12 slides, one-pager=5-section, objection=table+detail, demo=5-scene). 5. Tailor language and emphasis to buyer type (technical/economic/champion). 6. Deliver in the correct output format per asset type." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

